comments: McDaniels (MIN) is firming up over his right foot in Wagner's (ORL) path and does not deliver illegal contact during the screen.
Edwards (MIN) releases his off-arm away from Wagner's (ORL) side and marginal contact occurs near the free throw line.
Wagner (ORL) brings his left arm toward Edwards' (MIN) path and marginal contact occurs with Edwards' front/right arm during the drive.
Carter Jr. (ORL) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Isaac (ORL) jumps forward slightly and marginal contact occurs with Towns' (MIN) right side prior to when he cleanly dislodges the ball away from Towns during the inbound.
Isaac (ORL) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Gobert's (MIN) lower body is extended backward when he establishes himself in Wagner's (ORL) path and marginal contact occurs during the pick.
Suggs (ORL) initiates contact with Conley's (MIN) right forearm and affects his floater attempt.
Gobert's (MIN) left hand slightly extends forward toward Carter Jr.'s (ORL) back and marginal contact occurs as Carter Jr. elevates for the rebound.
Gobert (MIN) and Conley (MIN) each make contact with the ball prior to further marginal arm contact occurring with Carter Jr. (ORL) after Carter Jr. gains control of the rebound.

Gobert (MIN) lands short of Wagner (ORL) after being drawn into the air on the pump fake and marginal contact occurs as a result of Wagner slightly extending his right leg toward Gobert during the jump shot attempt.
Edwards (MIN) and Isaac (ORL) jump toward one another as they each pursue the rebound and marginal arm/body contact occurs as Isaac attempts the controlled tip.
Carter Jr. (ORL) initiates arm contact with Gobert (MIN) that affects his shot attempt near the rim.
Carter Jr. (ORL) brings his left forearm toward Gobert's (MIN) back and marginal contact occurs as Gobert retrieves the rebound and passes simultaneously.

Carter Jr. (ORL) establishes verticality prior to incidental body contact occurring with Edwards (MIN) at the end of the drive. Wagner's (ORL) right arm comes forward thereafter and further marginal contact occurs with Edwards' head after Edwards releases the pass. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Wagner (ORL) brings his hands outward toward McDaniels' (MIN) side and marginal contact occurs as McDaniels pursues the rebound.
McDaniels (MIN) turns slightly prior to marginal body contact occurring with Suggs (ORL) near midcourt.
McDaniels (MIN) cuts off the baseline and marginal body contact occurs with Suggs (ORL) when he tries to drive past him.
McDaniels (MIN) commits a take foul on Banchero (ORL).
Conley (MIN) does not inbound the ball within five seconds.
Banchero (ORL) legally contests Edwards' (MIN) jump shot attempt. Suggs (ORL) brings his left hand outward toward Edwards' side and marginal contact occurs with Edwards after the release.
Conley (MIN) commits a take foul on Isaac (ORL).
Suggs (ORL) and Conley (MIN) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Towns (MIN) attempts to commit a take foul on Suggs (ORL) and the contact is marginal.
